<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06192219 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06192219 </ACCESS><CAPTION>  Photo; PHOTO: Covington  </CAPTION><LEADPARA>  The Contra Costa County jury that convicted Julian Covington of thekidnapping, rape and murder of UC-Berkeley student Sally Mayne decided Tuesdayhe should be spared the death penalty and sentenced to life in prison withoutparole.;    The jury took less than two hours to arrive at their sentencingverdict for Covington, the first of two men to be tried for the March 11,1990, slaying of Mayne, a popular University of California athlete.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  MAN WHO KILLED STUDENT SPARED DEATH BY JURORS  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Bay Area in Brief  </MEMO><TEXT>     Mayne, 20, a third-year student at UC-Berkeley who was raised in Lafayette,was last seen by friends as she left a skating rink in Berkeley just aftermidnight on March 11, 1990. Her nude, battered body was found at a remoteshoreline area in Richmond early the same morning.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910710  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Wednesday  </DAY><MONTH>  July  </MONTH><PG.COL>  4B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><FEATURE>  PHOTO  </FEATURE><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  133  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Wednesday July 10, 199100192219,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>